<h2>Suspending a taxi rank</h2>


<p>If you would like to suspend a taxi rank then you must contact us first.</p>
<p>All taxi rank suspension requests are considered on a case-by-case basis. In order for us to consider your request, you must submit a fully completed taxi rank suspension form, along with any traffic management plans, to us at least 10 full working days before you would like the suspension to start. Saturdays, Sundays, Bank Holidays and public holidays are not counted as part of this period.</p>
<p>For some suspensions, a temporary taxi rank must be provided to ensure that there is still designated space for taxi drivers to provide a service to the public. This will take more than 10 working days to arrange and so where a temporary taxi rank is needed you should provide as much notice as possible.</p>
<p>Before you submit a request to suspend a taxi rank you must read our taxi rank suspension policy.</p>
<p><a href="mailto:tphranksinterchange&#64;tfl.gov.uk">Please email us your completed taxi rank suspension form</a>.
</p>
